history.content:
The requirements for honors-to-date on the COE website says:

Honors to date, or semester honors, is awarded if you:

  • Have completed a minimum of 12 units of letter grades on the Berkeley campus; and...

Do the 12 units have to be taken that semester (as with Dean's List) or is the requirement just overall in academic career? I'm taking under 12 letter-graded units this semester and was just wondering if I would still qualify.
history.subject: Honors-to-date Requirements
